[Comment "gm-rafael-leitaos-fight-the-slav-defense/course/3676, variation/118315"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Nc3 dxc4 {The Slav is one of black's most solid 
weapons against the Queen's Pawn. This Defence has been the favourite of many great 
players, especially World Champion Vassily Smyslov. It's not easy to gain an 
advantage against this variation, generally regarded as leading to extremely solid 
play. My suggestion aims to create some unbalanced play.} 5. a4 Bf5 6. Nh4 $5 {[%cal 
Bf3h4,Bh4f5][%csl Bf5] The main moves in this variation are 6. Ne5 and 6. e3. But the 
text move is very logical - white wants to capture the important light squared bishop 
and play with the center and the bishops pair. I have used this move very 
successfully. Now black has to decide if he allows this capture or not.} Be6 $6 7. e4 
{[%csl Bd4,Be4] and white is better, since the bishop is very badly placed at e6, 
hindering black's development.} *

