followed by Rad1, leaving all options open, including Bd2-e1-h4. It's really hard to 
decide which is best. In this position I offer two approaches.} 15. Qf2 $5 cxd4 16. 
exd4 Bxc3 $2 17. bxc3 Rxc3 18. Re1 $1 {[%csl Bf5,Bf7,Gc1,Ga2] At the cost of a mere 
pawn, white opened the position for the bishops. It is important to notice that the 
pawn deficit is no big deal, after all black has doubled pawns on the'f' file.} *

