again or simply play Bd2-Rad1 and then maybe Be1-h4. White will basically be doing 
one of this 3 plans in all positions.} 13. Kh1 {White must deploy some prophylaxis 
before trying to open the position. 13. e4 would to be too hasty due to Nb6!} c5 14. 
Ba2 {Another necessary prophylactic move.} Re8 $5 {It might seem dangerous to leave 
the f7 pawn unprotected when white has such a powerful bishop at a2. However, chess 
played at a good level is a very concrete game: you should disregard a natural move 
because of abstract considerations. Anyway white can fight for the advantage, 
although the f7 point doesn't have a major role for now.} 15. Nb5 $5 {One of the 
ideas of a6 is to avoid this move.} Qb6 16. dxc5 Bxc5 17. e4 $1 {Always this move!} 
fxe4 18. fxe4 Ne5 {For now black manages to defend any concrete threats, but white 
can play quietly and still fight for the initiative.} 19. Qe2 Nfg4 20. a5 Qa6 21. Bf4 
{With a complicated fight ahead.} *

